"'''The Breath of Gelgelar'''" is a short story written by [[Jean Rabe]] with illustrations by [[Brian Schomburg]], originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 14|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 14]] by [[West End Games]] in [[August]] [[1997]], and has since been released online at [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
[[T'laerean Larn|T'laerean]], a young [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] [[Force Adept]], has the ability to experience the senses of a wild [[Reeho (bird)|reeho bird]] and occupy its mind as a “passenger”, but he cannot break [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] connection without coming into physical contact with the bird. Thus, when the bird is captured, T'laerean begins to panic. The bird [[Death/Legends|dies]] at the claws of a predator, and T'laerean nearly dies himself but is eased back into consciousness by his mentor, the [[Wise Man of Kooroo]].

